label.value: evidence information from observational drug-drug interaction study

definition.value: An evidence information content entity that is about an assay that realizes an observation design and has at least two drug products as a specified input, and that focuses on pharmacokinetics in an organism.

label.value: public adverse event reporting database

definition.value: A data set that is structured and stored on a computer and that is publicly available and contains reports of adverse events.

label.value: evidence information from a publicly reported observation-based adverse drug event report

definition.value: An evidence information content entity that is about an assay that was triggered by an adverse drug event, and that is part on a publicly accessible database for adverse event reporting.

label.value: evidence information from an observation-based case-report of a drug interaction

definition.value: An evidence information content entity that is about an assay that was triggered by an adverse drug event following the administration of at least two drugs.

label.value: adverse drug reaction causality evaluation protocol

definition.value: A protocol that specifies methodology to assess the likelihood of a drug to be the cause for an adverse event by answering a set of questions about the drug reaction report.

label.value: evidence information from an evaluated observation-based case-report of a drug interaction

definition.value: An evidence information content entity that is about an assay that was triggered by an adverse drug event following the administration of at least two drugs, and that is the specified outcome of a adverse drug reaction causality evaluation.

label.value: clearance measurement datum

definition.value: A measurement datum that is the specified output of measuring the volume of plasma that is completely cleared off of a substance per unit time.

label.value: fold

definition.value: A dimensionless ratio unit which describes the relation between the two numbers x and y by giving the multiplier necessary to make x equal to y.

label.value: pharmacokinetic parameter ratio directionality

definition.value: An information content entity that is part of a pharmacokinetic parameter ratio and that describes whether the relationship between the numbers of the ratio is a positive or a negative one.

label.value: area under the curve ratio

definition.value: A pharmacokinetic parameter ratio that describes the relation between the pharmacokinetic area under the curve (AUC) for a given active ingredient or metabolite in an organism with and without the inhibiting drug present in the organism.

label.value: renal clearance ratio

definition.value: A pharmacokinetic parameter ratio that describes the relation between the measurement of the volume of blood, serum, or plasma from which an active ingredient or a metabolite is completely removed by the kidney in a given amount of time in an organism with and without the inhibiting drug present in the organism.

label.value: pharmacokinetic parameter ratio

definition.value: An information content entity that describes the relationship between the mean (arithmetic and geometric) of measurements of a pharmacokintect parameter for a given drug A in absence of another drug and the mean (arithmetic and geometric) of measurements of a pharmacokintect parameter for a given drug A coadministrated with another drug B.

label.value: pharmacokinetic parameter ratio decrease

definition.value: An pharmacokinetic parameter directionality that describes negative relationship between the numbers of the ratio.

label.value: pharmacokinetic parameter ratio increase

definition.value: An pharmacokinetic parameter directionality that describes positive relationship between the numbers of the ratio.

label.value: drug maximum concentration ratio

definition.value: A pharmacokinetic parameter ratio that describes the relation between the drug maximum concentration measurements for a given active ingredient or metabolite in an organism with and without the inhibiting drug present in the organism.

label.value: half-life ratio

definition.value: A pharmacokinetic parameter ratio that describes the relation between the time it takes for half of a given active ingredient or metabolite to be removed from the system of an organism with and without the inhibiting drug present in the organism.

label.value: hepatic clearance ratio

definition.value: A pharmacokinetic parameter ratio that describes the relation between the measurement of the volume of blood, serum, or plasma from which an active ingredient or a metabolite is completely removed by the liver in a given amount of time in an organism with and without the inhibiting drug present in the organism.

label.value: bioavailability ratio

definition.value: A pharmacokinetic parameter ratio that describes the relation between the measurement of the fraction of the administered dose of an unaltered drug that reaches systemic circulation in the abscene of another drug, and the the measurement of the fraction of the administered dose of an unaltered drug that reaches systemic circulation when coadministered with another drug.
